article.headline: Manhattan 69, Wagner 56
article.story: NEW YORK (AP) -- Devon Austin scored nine points during a 24-0 second-half run for Manhattan to help the Jaspers beat Wagner 69-56 on Wednesday night. Trailing 41-36 with 12:43 left, Manhattan scored the next 24 points to put the game away. Patrick Bouli led Manhattan (2-0) with 20 points. Austin added 15. Jamal Smith scored 16 points to lead Wagner (1-1).
